-- Cotton on ICE Futures Jumps to Record $1.306 a Pound on Supply Concerns
-- B y   J a e   H u r
-- 2010-11-02T01:04:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/cotton-on-ice-futures-jumps-to-record-1-306-a-pound-on-supply-concerns.html
Cotton on ICE Futures U.S. in New
York jumped to a record on concern that global supplies will
trail demand further after cold weather in China and storms in
the U.S. hurt crops.  Futures for December delivery advanced 1 percent to $1.306
a pound, the highest level since the fiber started trading 140
years ago, before trading at $1.300 as of 10:01 a.m. Tokyo time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jae Hur in Singapore at 
